5:
Huh! So this is what a summer
festival in Yamato is like. Really feels
like we're in a whole new world!
8:
I've seen plenty of festivals on my
adventures, but nothing quite like
this.
11:
Tell that to Inaho. She worked really
hard setting this up!
15:
Of course! She even picked out this
yukata thing for me to wear, too.
18:
It's a good fit... You look like a man
with sophisticated tastes!
22:
Haha, thanks. I like wearing things
like this from time to time.
25:
Hey there, you two! If you're just
gonna stand around flappin' your
gums, why don't you try my takoyaki!
28:
Guess we ARE just standin' around,
huh? Come, Alk, adventure awaits!
35:
Ouch... Probably should've waited for
that takoyaki to cool down first.
Tasty, though!
42:
I mean, those things have octopus
in them. A lot of people get turned
off by the tentacles.
45:
I'm an adventurer, Alk! We'll even eat
monster meat if that's all we've got. I
even know someone who
specializes in cooking the stuff.
48:
There are others like us? Wow... I'd
like to meet that person one day.
51:
I could arrange that! Always fun
introducin' people to a comrade I
can brag about.
54:
Someone YOU can brag about?
They really must be something...
58: What? I'm talking about you, Alk.
61:
You started out as a fledgling that
could hardly fight, but you've since
traveled to other worlds and now
fight with a crew that's as tough as
they come.
63:
It's easy to brag about someone like
you, Alk.
66:
Heh... It's a little embarrassing to get
praise like that.
71:
All that said, you're still pretty terrible
with the ladies, eh?
75: C-come on! I didn't deserve that!
78:
Oh, my! Is that Leon and Alk I'm
seeing?
81:
Kikuno! Fancy meeting you here. You
enjoying the festival?
84:
Hehe! I am having fun, though not
as a spectator.
87:
There's a special teahouse near this
place that I've worked at in the past.
I am helping out tonight.
90:
A special teahouse, eh? Consider
my interest piqued.
93:
Mm-hmm! I have not even rolled
out the tatami mats so far...
97:
But... I would be happy to get things
ready in a hurry for you two!
107:
Alk. Buddy. A brave adventurer like
yourself shouldn't fear the unknown.
112:
Go ahead, make fun of me. I'm still
not going!
117:
You there, woman. How much are
you charging?
120:
Oh, my! Your approach leaves much
to be desired, my dear.
123:
S-surely you do not mean to say I
am... unrefined?
126:
Indeed. If you wish to make use of
my services, I suggest you bring
along someone who can... show you
the ropes.
129:
Know your place! Watch your
tongue, or we shall relieve you of it!
133:
Oh, nooo! Isn't there a strong man
who will SAVE me?
140: Hah! She wants us to show off, eh?
143:
That's enough, boys. Telling
someone to know their place
doesn't seem very refined to me.
145:
You listening, buddy? You take your
friends along on nights like these,
not your attendants.
150:
Waving your swords around at a
festival isn't making you any
classier, guys. Can we just get this
over with already?
153: Y-you fool! Pay for your insolence!
160:
But... I cannot allow them to
challenge you on their own.
166: You've got guts, kid. I'll give you that.
170:
I suppose I can give you a lesson on
how to properly treat a woman.
173: How's that sound to you, Kikuno?
177:
Well, I DID say he should bring
someone to show him the ropes...
181:
And this young man showed
bravery, so the least I can do is show
him some hospitality.
192:
Relax and get your mind outta the
gutter. We're just gonna drink and
be merry!
197:
I-I don't know what you're talking
about!
201:
Hehe, for your information, the
teahouse I mentioned is also
famous for its cuisine.
210:
Haha, well all right, then! The night
has only just begun, but...
214:
This is shaping up to be one hell of a
festival!
